oard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why the powergaming mindset?</span><hr size=1> Hey, our 54 bard got her lute from Maestro last weekend (thank you to CoFE and Phoenix <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), and do you know what she was wearing at the time?  Lambent, Faydark Ringmail, a fine steel breastplate, and the Twilight hat and bracers... (she does have SS boots from her excusrions to Karnor's) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Not everyone's ubered out, even in this day and age, nor is uber equipment necessary to do these areas that, in the past, no-one had Velious gear for.<br>
<br>
Sometimes, when I'm running around with my little evil enchanter (L 17 now), I marvel at how easy the zones she is exping in seem compared to when Nydia and Faervas were getting their butts handed to them daily.  Part of that is knowing the zones and your class capabilities better.  But a huge part of it is the fact that my alt is better dressed at 17 than Nydia was at 40...<br>
<br>
Unrest in full level 45 twink gear is a whole different experience than it is in a raw silk robe/banded &amp; rawhide and those uber +2 int &amp; +2 wis rings you just made yourself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Some people claim that the new additions to the game have 'dumbed it down' that much more at the lower levels.  It is true that the new corpse pre L 10 rules, and the avilability of rezzes at level 14 save a LOT of hiking.  But if you want to test out the game 'easiness' out, make an alt and level it from 1-20 with no outside equipment or levelling assistance whatsoever, and see if those lions don't still hit hard.  I've got a little ranger in thorn mail quest armor, a bronze shortsword, and scraps he looted off orc pawns, he looks just like the little green Sprout <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) who is getting his butt handed to him daily <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  <br>
<br>
EQ can be still be fun and challenging at all levels, even in the face of rampant mudflation.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  And to the newer players out there, as long as you are enjoying what you are doing, don't worry about how someone else plays *their* game...<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
Nydia Ywalmoriel<br>
Autonomous Collective<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uburnesalot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Burnesalot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 3:27:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why the powergaming mindset?</span><hr size=1> When i started playing, about the time velious came out, i had 3 RL friends playing, 51war, 35druid &amp; 27ranger. <br>
no matter how much i pleaded with them they wouldnt PL me, although the druid (wonko) would help me do sol ro temple quest armor, yay.<br>
<br>
im so glad they made me lvl the hard way, if i was PL i prolly woulda lost interest in the game at about lvl 52 when expin starts to get hard <p><IMG SRC="http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~peq/ayonaero/ubb/uploads/kikisig.jpg">
<br>
<IMG SRC="http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~peq/ayonaero/ubb/uploads/slain.JPG">
<br>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=203377>My Magelo</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uailwon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ailwon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 3:15:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why the powergaming mindset?</span><hr size=1> Hehe...I try hard NOT to level, now.  When I get a toon to 50, I pretty much have to retire it, I just don't have time to play the post-50 game :'(<br>
<br>
Ailwon Ravenwind, 52 Ranger - Retired <br>
Thurogard Justicebringer, 40 Paladin <p>"For he who shall, so shall he who"<BR> - Puke&Snot</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/unydiaywalmoriel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nydia Ywalmoriel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/4/02 10:41:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why the powergaming mindset?</span><hr size=1> Many classes can solo to 60, if they are not threatened by PvP; not only solo, but solo in WW or DN or the Grey or Akheva.  Also, the new 'channel' system enables people to do 'contract work', if you will, if they wish to see raid level areas without joining a large guild (and the raiding committments these usually require).  Since my own guild containes only 5 level 50+ people (most of our guild is casual players), almost all of my own raid experience, such as it is, has been gained by either freelancing or as a multi-guild thing.  Also, I don't know what the custom was on your former server, but here on A Ro a person in the process of applying to most of the raid level guilds on the server are not allowed to be tagged by any other guild, so many of the 'guildless' folks you see around may be in transition.  Finally, some folks (including myself) find very large raids uninteresting, and don't feel that we're 'missing' anything by not ever getting the chance to take down AoW or see Vex Thal, if you know what I mean... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
Nydia Ywalmoriel<br>
Autonomous Collective <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/unydiaywalmoriel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nydia Ywalmoriel</A> at: 8/4/02 10:45:13 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usaintsaens.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saintsaens</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wanderer</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/5/02 1:11:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why the powergaming mindset?</span><hr size=1> Well, on TZ, most people were required to raid with their prospective guildmates, which I assume is the custom here as well.  My problem is, I cannot stand not being in a guild.  I miss guildchat, and I miss having people to talk to (otherwise I bug my /friends list constantly, just ask Narf :)).<br>
<br>
I also don't see the point of soloing to 60, but then again this is coming from my personal beliefs.  If I am forced to solo, I kill 2 mobs and am bored almost to tears.  I much prefer being in a group or at the very least having a partner to have someone to talk to than being by myself medding for 10 minutes.  Also I find when you're in a good group, exp seems to flow faster, especially if you're taking out red and yellow mobs with ease.<br>
<br>
Again, I don't see how large scale raids can be &quot;uninteresting,&quot; but that's probably the powergamer in me talking.  To me, the game is about helping myself and my guildmates kill high end mobs, and the challenge involved in getting quests done or zones cleared.  I know there's lots of lag on raids, and not everyone walks away from a raid with something, but there's the fact that I'm helping others that makes a raid interesting for me.<br>
<br>
Saintsaens <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/unydiaywalmoriel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nydia Ywalmoriel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/5/02 4:03:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why the powergaming mindset?</span><hr size=1> Personally, I don't like soloing either, except occasionally to test my limits; as an enchanter, small groups are where the most 'fun' and action is, imho.  But I do know people who largely soloed their way to 60; and some are actually competent players.  And while I respect the organization and the effort that goes into large target raids, as well as what they are able to accomplish, it's just not my scene (one man's meat being another man's poison, and all).  If it can be done with 3 groups or less (4 being tops for me, after that it just starts to feel like a mob scene, not to mention being overkill for most of the encounters I participate in), I'm all for it; and you'd be surprised what you can do with 15 people in mostly crap gear with an average level of 55, if you have folks who are flexible and on the ball.  My own little guild's raids are usually even smaller, averaging 8 peeps of avg level 46 these days, but we are just starting to get to the high end Kunark dungeons (worked Seb and HS keys this week, Faer and I made our first trip to HS), and into Kael arena, which is very exciting for us.  We've completed several Twilight quest armor pieces for every sub-50 main in the guild (which have unique graphics, our 21st level cleric gets asked all the time about his violet armor, which belonged to the late Eanaman), and our Ranger made her Rallic pack tonight <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
What can I say, for some of us it's the journey... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
Nydia Ywalmoriel<br>
Autonomous Collective<br>
<br>
P.S. While I've never 'pledged' any of the major guilds on this server, the usual protocol here seems to be that if you are 'pledging' a guild, you are required to raid with them, but are only allowed to wear the tag during the raid at first, and must remove it afterward...<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utheperfectflaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThePerfectFlaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druidhugger</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/6/02 11:02:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why the powergaming mindset?</span><hr size=1> I never really understood the reasoning behind using &quot;someone to talk to&quot; as a validation for not solo'ing.<br>
<br>
Then again, maybe I'm the only one who has discovered the &quot;/tell&quot; function.  8(<br>
<br>
