<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Edit: sig deleted - too big. Rules are: 150 high, 450 wide, no greater than 50kb.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ualbarath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Albarath</A> at: 8/6/02 11:08:18 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uwonderbiff.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wonderbiff</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wanderer</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/6/02 10:48:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why the powergaming mindset?</span><hr size=1> I introduced my RL workmate to eq about 2 years after I started.  I twinked him to make his life easier and PL him every once in a while to help him move up to the higher level stuff but I like to give space to him to see what he likes and dislikes.  He now has about 14 characters on 2 accounts no lie all between 6 and 36.  He equips his characters with every spell and takes great care to understand other classes but mainly my point is I didn't want to cheat him of the 1-50 levels but help him enjoy the benifits of high level friends.  <br>
<br>
Mainly if your of the raid mindset go for it level level level if not just toss your tube on the stream and go for a ride. The thing that causes most of us to say level level level is we hear you complain I can't do that...  If your not complaining you should rairly hear some one say level.<br>
<br>
I myself have enjoyed all of it at the same time and don't think I will change.. raid a couple times a week, level a bit and quest a bit.  Although I think leveling is primary to reduce the time it takes for you to do anything leveling is not a requirement. <br>
AB <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usaintsaens.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saintsaens</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wanderer</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/6/02 11:43:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why the powergaming mindset?</span><hr size=1> PerfectFlaw,<br>
<br>
Ask Narf (the very first person I added to my friends list on this server) about how I'd constantly do /who all friends just to have someone to talk to :) (I've stopped that now, sort of, now that I have people to talk to)<br>
<br>
I constantly bug my friends list (well, not bug, but send tells to them), even though I'm now in a guild.  I am a social person.  I crave contact, people to talk to, joke around with, stuff like that.  That is what I see a guild as being for, along with being able to help people do stuff they aren't able to do (such as a higher lvl quest, an epic, a large scale raid) alone.<br>
<br>
Then again, this is just me and my playing style.  I'm not saying it's the only method, and that the game allows for people to solo to 60, but I just cannot understand why people would want to, if they want to do all they can with the game.<br>
